{
  "texts": [
    "Because the amount of training data requires a large volume, Nozza et al. [153] use three pre-training models simultaneously, namely Wiki2Vec, GoogleNews (W2V), and BERT.",
    "Most domain adaptation methods focus on one domain without considering all annotations.",
    "When there is a shift between domains too large, the decline in NER performance is even more significant.",
    "This weakness is corrected by the method proposed by Li et al.",
    "taking multi-aspect relevance learning (MARL) [152]."
  ]
}